-- Renault to Set `More Realistic' Targets, Chief Executive Ghosn Tells Monde
-- B y   S t e v e   R h i n d s
-- 2010-09-29T09:22:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/renault-to-set-more-realistic-targets-chief-executive-ghosn-tells-monde.html
Renault SA, France’s second-biggest
carmaker, will set “more realistic” targets than in the past,
Chief Executive Officer Carlos Ghosn said in an interview
published in French daily Le Monde.  Ghosn said his company still has the potential to do “a
lot of things” with General Motors Co. “where there are a lot
of savings,” according to the newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Rhinds at 
 srhinds@bloomberg.net  